= Origin and Relationships

- *Archaeopteryx lithographica*: The earliest known bird fossil (147 million years old).
  - Demonstrated phylogenetic relatedness of birds and *theropod dinosaurs*.
  - Had reptilian skeleton (long bony tail, clawed fingers, abdominal ribs) but possessed *feathers*.

#figure(
  image(images.at("figure-27-1").path, width: 80%),
  caption: images.at("figure-27-1").caption
)

- *Evolutionary History*:
  - Birds are archosaurs, sharing derived characters with dromeosaurs (e.g., *Velociraptor*): furcula (fused clavicles), lunate wrist bones.
  - Living birds (*Neornithes*) are divided into:
    - *Paleognathae*: Flightless ostrich-like birds (ratites) and tinamous. Flat sternum (except tinamous).
    - *Neognathae*: All other birds, mostly flying, with a keeled sternum.

